gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Celtics 140, Warriors 88
gameRecap.excerpt: The Celtics win their 11th straight game as they defeat the Warriors, 140-88. Jaylen Brown (29 points, five 3PM) and Jayson Tatum (27 points, five assists, four 3PM) combined for 56 points for the Celtics in the victory, while Lester Quinones tallied a team-high 17 points, along with five rebounds for the Warriors in the losing effort. The Celtics improve to 48-12 on the season and 29-3 on their home floor, while the Warriors fall to 32-28.
